Title: Leaders' Use of Moral Justifications Increases Policy Support
Description: We are examining whether, holding a policy constant, leaders who justify policies using moral or pragmatic justifications generate more third-party support for their policies. A secondary goal is to elucidate the mechanism responsible for any main effects of policy frame.
Contributors: Alex Van Zant, Don Moore, Tetlock
Tags: 

Leaders' Use of Moral Justifications Increases Policy Support
We are examining whether, holding a policy constant, leaders who justify policies using moral or pragmatic justifications generate more third-party support for their policies. A secondary goal is to elucidate the mechanism responsible for any main effects of policy frame.
